RUSH et al. v. BAILEY. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. February 10, 1903.) No. 1,203. Appeal from the Circuit Court of the United States for the Northern District of Mississippi.

Before PARDEE and SHELBY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

As neither of the judges who participated in the decision of this case desires a rehearing, but each is still satisfied with the justice and equity of the decision as rendered, the application for rehearing is denied.
